[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_8qw52")
reagent_id = "Na"
title = "Sodium"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Symbol:[/cell][cell]Na[/cell]
[cell]Element:[/cell][cell]Sodium[/cell]
[cell]Atomic number:[/cell][cell]11[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]23 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid metal[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Soft, shiny silver metal (when freshly cut)[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Important properties[/b]
• A very reactive metal.
• Belongs to the alkali metals group.
• Soft — can be cut with a knife.
• Reacts quickly with water and air.
[b]Where sodium is found[/b]
• In table salt (NaCl).
• In seawater.
• In many minerals and compounds.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of chemicals and compounds.
• Used in sodium lamps for street lighting.
• Important in industry and chemical reactions.
[b]Safety[/b]
Sodium reacts violently with water and must be stored under oil to prevent contact with air and moisture."
